Rating: 4
Easy entertaining! Serve with spanish or dirty rice and "Corn and Bell Pepper Salad" (B.A. July 1990). My own tips: I use 1/3 cup of kosher salt in the brine instead of 1/2 cup (otherwise, the chops are too salty). I also skip the step of seasoning the chops with salt and pepper before rubbing in the spice rub -- instead, I add some fresh ground black pepper to the spice rub mixture. I make double the spice rub mixture (or at least 1 1/2 times the recipe). Be sure to drain and pat dry the chops real well and rub in the spice rub just before grilling, otherwise, the sugar in the rub becomes runny. Add mesquite chips to the coals for more of a smoky flavor. The chops improve with age and taste even better the next day if you can wait that long! Enjoy!

